{"abstract":[{"text":"The enhanced PDFKit framework lets your app perform essential operations, such as authoring, modifying, and displaying Portable Document Format (PDF) files. Previously available only on macOS, this powerful framework is now available on iOS 11. Gain insights and best practices on how to use this technology within your own apps.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10089-Whats-new-in-PDFKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-221-Introducing-PencilKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-721-Combine-in-Practice"],"style":"list","type":"links"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/241\/"}},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-241-introducing-pdfkit-on-ios"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-241-Introducing-PDFKit-on-iOS","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Introducing PDFKit on iOS","roleHeading":"WWDC17","role":"sampleCode"},"references":{"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}],"role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"type":"topic","title":"WWDC17","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-721-Combine-in-Practice":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-721-Combine-in-Practice","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-721-combine-in-practice","title":"Combine in Practice","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Expand your knowledge of Combine, Apple’s new unified, declarative framework for processing values over time. Learn about how to correctly handle errors, schedule work and integrate Combine into your app today."}],"type":"topic","kind":"article"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC22-10089-Whats-new-in-PDFKit":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10089-Whats-new-in-PDFKit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover PDFKit — a full-featured framework that helps your app view, edit, and save PDF documents. We’ll take you through the latest features in PDFKit, including support for live text and forms, creating PDFs from images, building interactive overlays, and saving annotations."}],"title":"What’s new in PDFKit","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc22-10089-whats-new-in-pdfkit","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"title":"WWDC Notes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-221-Introducing-PencilKit":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-221-introducing-pencilkit","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-221-Introducing-PencilKit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Meet PencilKit, Apple’s feature-rich drawing and annotation framework. With just a few lines of code, you can add a full drawing experience to your app — with access to a canvas, responsive inks, rich tool palette and drawing model. Hear the technical details that make a great Apple Pencil experience. Learn about the new screenshot editor and how you can adopt just a few small APIs to enable your full content to be captured beyond the size of the screen, with or without your app’s user interface."}],"type":"topic","title":"Introducing PencilKit"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2017/241/":{"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/241\/","type":"download","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/241\/"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","variants":[{"traits"